HEADWORD: Annihilationist
<hw>An*ni`hi*la"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Theol.)</fld>
<def>One who believes that eternal punishment consists in annihilation
or extinction of being; a destructionist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

